<section id="research" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
  <!-- Title -->
  <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl mb-12">
      Research
  </h2>

  <!-- 1. Broad Research Areas -->
  <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 mb-16">
    <article class="rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-600/80 to-purple-600/80 p-6 text-white shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Quantum &amp;‚ÄØSemiclassical Gravity</h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Planck‚Äëscale quantum effects and their imprint on classically curved space‚Äëtime.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-600/80 to-teal-600/80 p-6 text-white shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Black‚ÄëHole Physics</h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Interior structure, horizon thermodynamics and information retention.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-600/80 to-yellow-500/80 p-6 text-white shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Quantum Geometry</h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Covariant uncertainty principles and Wick‚Äërotated metric phases.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-600/80 to-pink-600/80 p-6 text-white shadow-lg">
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Early‚ÄëUniverse Cosmology</h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Geometric mechanisms capable of seeding, driving and ending cosmic inflation.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <!-- 2. Core Questions & Long‚ÄëTerm Vision -->
  <div class="prose prose-lg lg:prose-xl mb-16">
    <h3>Core Research Questions&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Long‚ÄëTerm Goals</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Can space‚Äëtime singularities be removed within a covariant semiclassical framework?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>What are the truly relativistic limits of quantum uncertainty?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>How does Wick rotation encode thermodynamics and quantum phases of gravity?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Does curvature itself decohere quantum matter?</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-6 italic">
      <span class="font-semibold">Vision&nbsp;‚ü∂</span>
      A covariant, experimentally anchored picture of quantum space‚Äëtime where horizons,
      curvature and quantum information are treated on equal footing¬†‚Äî linking black‚Äëhole
      interiors, Planck‚Äëscale physics and the dynamics of the early universe.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- 3. Current Work & Selected Outputs -->
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-8">Current Work &amp; Selected Outputs</h3>
  <div class="columns-1 sm:columns-2 lg:columns-3 gap-6 space-y-6">
    <a href="https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevD.105.L101501" class="block break-inside-avoid rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-md transition hover:shadow-lg">
      <h4 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Relativistic GUP</h4>
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        First coordinate‚Äëfree formulation of the Generalised Uncertainty Principle, tightening phenomenological bounds.
      </p>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-medium text-indigo-600">Phys.‚ÄØRev.‚ÄØD¬†105¬†(2022)</span>
    </a>
    <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2010.01822" class="block break-inside-avoid rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-md transition hover:shadow-lg">
      <h4 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Covariant&nbsp;Wick Rotation</h4>
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Shows how Euclidean ‚Äúcaps‚Äù on Lorentzian manifolds encode horizon entropy and path‚Äëintegral phases.
      </p>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-medium text-indigo-600">EPJ¬†C¬†83¬†(2023)</span>
    </a>
    <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.09038" class="block break-inside-avoid rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-md transition hover:shadow-lg">
      <h4 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Quantum Decoherence in Curved Space‚ÄëTime</h4>
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Derives curvature‚Äëdependent decoherence times, suggesting satellite‚Äëbased experimental tests.
      </p>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-medium text-indigo-600">arXiv¬†2302.09038</span>
    </a>
    <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.02944" class="block break-inside-avoid rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-md transition hover:shadow-lg">
      <h4 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Black‚ÄëHole Interior Modelling</h4>
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Two‚Äëphase quasiparticle core that avoids the central singularity while respecting horizon thermodynamics.
      </p>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-medium text-indigo-600">arXiv¬†2506.02944</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- 4. Ongoing Directions -->
  <div class="prose prose-lg lg:prose-xl mt-16">
    <h3>In¬†Progress</h3>
    <details class="group">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer text-xl font-semibold">
        Singularity‚ÄëAvoiding Black‚ÄëHole Interiors
        <span class="ml-2 inline-block rotate-0 transition group-open:rotate-90">‚ñ∏</span>
      </summary>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Extending the quasiparticle‚Äëcore model to include quantum back‚Äëreaction from Hawking partners,
        aiming for a horizon‚Äëto‚Äëcenter description embedded in effective field theory.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="group">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer text-xl font-semibold">
        Geometric Models of Inflation
        <span class="ml-2 inline-block rotate-0 transition group-open:rotate-90">‚ñ∏</span>
      </summary>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Using covariant Wick‚Äërotated metrics to construct ‚ÄúEuclidean bridge‚Äù geometries that interpolate
        between pre‚Äëinflationary and FRW epochs, offering naturally graceful exit conditions.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>
